!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = cell type: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = library type: mRNA
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = genotype: APOE: E3/E4
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = treatment: lecanemab 10 mg/kg bi-weekly
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = aria status: Control
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = infusion#: 17
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = age: 75-79
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = Sex: F
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = mmse: 24
!Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1 = Patients received bi-weekly intravenous infusions of lecanemab (10 mg/kg). Blood was collected immediately prior to infusion.
!Sample_growth_protocol_ch1 = PBMCs were isolated from whole blood using density gradient centrifugation with SepMate tubes. Cells were washed, counted, and cryopreserved in 90% FBS/10% DMSO in liquid nitrogen.
!Sample_molecule_ch1 = polyA RNA
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = Cryopreserved PBMCs were thawed at 37C and resuspended in RPMI-1640 + 10% FBS for immediate processing.
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = 10x Genomics Chromium Single Cell 5 prime v2 with TotalSeq-C CITE-seq (137 antibodies). Gene expression and ADT libraries from same cDNA. V(D)J libraries enriched using 10x Human T Cell V(D)J kit.
!Sample_description = Library name: Patient1_GEX
!Sample_description = PBMCs from female AD patient (age 75-79y) with APOE E3/E4, lecanemab treatment, ARIA status negative (control), infusion #17, gene expression library
!Sample_data_processing = Illumina NovaSeq 6000. GEX: 28bp R1, 90bp R2. ADT: 28bp R1, 90bp R2. VDJ: 150bp R1, 150bp R2.
!Sample_data_processing = Cell Ranger multi v9.0.1, GRCh38 reference. QC: <10% mitochondrial genes, doublet removal (scDblFinder v1.20.2), ambient RNA correction (decontX v1.4.1). Integration: Seurat v5.3.0 with SCTransform. Cell types: multimodal RNA+protein with weighted nearest neighbor analysis. VDJ: scRepertoire v2.3.4.
!Sample_data_processing = Assembly: GRCh38
!Sample_data_processing = Supplementary files format and content: H5 matrices with gene expression and ADT counts. VDJ: clonotypes, filtered contigs. Cell annotations include cell types and UMAP coordinates. TotalSeq-C antibody panel provided.
